{
  "doc_id": "31329",
  "text": "The presence and absence of 16 distinct KIR genes was determined using our recently developed duplex sequencespecific priming-based polymerase chain reaction (SSP-PCR) typing system [CITATION_1] ). The unique and unusual KIR genotypes were further confirmed by re-typing using our alternative SSP-PCR typing method [CITATION_2] ). Both of the typing methods were validated extensively using the UCLA International KIR exchange reference DNA samples, which provided identical KIR genotyping results, indicating that the specificity and sensitivity of the two methods were comparable [CITATION_3] ).",
